%% Sequence: Session Lifecycle E2E (Fase 3)
%% Assistant envía resumen, backoffice persiste y actualiza estado
sequenceDiagram
    participant Assistant as Assistant
    participant API as Backoffice API
    participant Summary as Summary Service
    participant Echelon as Echelon Service
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant Cache as KV Cache

    Note over Assistant,Cache: Assistant valida dispositivo
    Assistant->>API: GET /auth/devices/:machineId
    API-->>Assistant: accessToken, expiresAt

    Note over Assistant,Cache: Obtener contexto
    Assistant->>API: GET /context/:echelonId<br/>Header: Authorization Bearer accessToken (o JWT usuario)
    API->>Cache: getContextBundleFromCache(echelonId)
    alt miss
        API->>Summary: getContextBundle (vía context-bundle.service)
        API->>Cache: setContextBundleCache
    end
    API-->>Assistant: context bundle

    Note over Assistant,Cache: Enviar resumen (idempotent)
    Assistant->>API: POST /sessions/:sessionId/summary<br/>Idempotency-Key, { rawContent?, embedding? }
    API->>DB: create summary (o createWithEmbedding si embedding)
    API->>Cache: invalidateContextCache(echelonId)
    alt echelon en OPEN (primera sesión con summary)
        API->>Echelon: transition(echelonId, START_SESSION)
        Echelon->>DB: updateState(IN_PROGRESS)
    end
    API-->>Assistant: 201 { data: summary }

    Note over Assistant,Cache: Registrar uso (idempotent)
    Assistant->>API: POST /api/v1/usage<br/>Idempotency-Key, { monthYear, tokens, costCents, productId?, echelonId? }
    API->>DB: recordUsage (upsert)
    API-->>Assistant: 201 { data: usageRecord }

    Note over Assistant,Cache: Flujo posterior: consolidación y cierre (Fase 4)
